<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br><br>
When you use another person&#8217;s ideas or words in your writing, list the author&#8217;s name, in parentheses, immediately following the cited material.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	It was found&hellip; (Atkin). 
</blockquote>
<br><br>
Or include the author&#8217;s names in your sentence.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Atkin found that&hellip;
</blockquote>
